
“Helm is the package manager for Kubernetes that simplifies application deployment and management. 
Instead of manually applying multiple YAML files for Deployments, Services, ConfigMaps, and Ingress,  Helm allows these files to be bundled together into a
single package called a Helm Chart

A Helm Chart has a standard structure with Chart.yaml for metadata, values.yaml for configurations, templates/ for Kubernetes manifests 
with placeholders, and an optional charts/ folder for dependencies. This makes manifests reusable and parameterized,

so we only update values.yaml instead of editing every file.we can deploy the same application across Dev, Staging, and Production without rewriting code.

Helm provides Release Management. Every time you install or upgrade a chart, Helm creates a new revision. 
It tracks changes in a history log, allowing you to perform instant rollbacks to a previous stable state if something goes wrong.

So overall, Helm reduces complexity, enforces consistency, improves scalability, and makes Kubernetes deployments production-ready.”

_________________________
for commands
helm install [name] [chart] (To deploy)

helm upgrade [name] [chart] (To update)

helm rollback [name] [revision] (To fix a mistake)

______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
A typical Helm chart structure looks like this:

jio-stg-om-chart/
  ├── Chart.yaml        # Metadata about the chart
  ├── values.yaml       # Default configuration values for templates
  ├── charts/           # Subcharts (if any)
  └── templates/        # Template files for Kubernetes resources
      ├── deployment.yaml   
      ├── service.yaml
      └── pv.yaml
_____________________________________________________________________________________
 Values.yaml 
---------------

You can customize deployments by creating your own values.yaml file, overriding default values in the chart:

stgvalues.yaml
----
replicaCount: 2
image:
  repository: my-repo/my-app
  tag: "1.0.0"
service:
  type: LoadBalancer
  port: 80
request:
 cpu: 1
 memory: 12Gi

prod-values.yaml
-----

replicaCount: 5
image:
  repository: my-repo/my-app-prod
  tag: "1.1.0"
service:
  type: LoadBalancer
  port: 80
request:
 cpu: 8
 memory: 128Gi

